               <p>462. 
               
                  <persName id="t17950916-92-defend962" type="defendantName">
                     MARY 
                     MOORE
                  <interp inst="t17950916-92-defend962" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-defend962" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-defend962" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-defend962" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17950916-92-off519" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-off519" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-off519" type="offenceSubcategory" value="shoplifting"></interp>
               feloniously stealing, on the <rs id="t17950916-92-cd520" type="crimeDate">10th of September</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950916-92-off519 t17950916-92-cd520"></join>, nine yards of printed cotton, value 12s the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17950916-92-victim964" type="victimName">
                           Robert 
                           MacGlew
                        <interp inst="t17950916-92-victim964" type="surname" value="MacGlew"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17950916-92-victim964" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17950916-92-victim964" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950916-92-off519 t17950916-92-victim964"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , privately on his shop
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17950916-92-person965">
                  ROBERT
                   MAC GLEW
               <interp inst="t17950916-92-person965" type="surname" value="MAC GLEW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-person965" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-person965" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I live in <placeName id="t17950916-92-crimeloc521">Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17950916-92-crimeloc521" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17950916-92-crimeloc521" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950916-92-off519 t17950916-92-crimeloc521"></join>, a <rs id="t17950916-92-viclabel522" type="occupation">linen draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950916-92-victim964 t17950916-92-viclabel522"></join>; the prisoner at the bar came into my shop on Thursday, the 10th of September, a little after eight in the evening, and desired to look at some printed callico for a gown, I shewed her several, she did not fix on any of them, she desired me to shew her some at all wide; I shewed her several of them, she did not fix on any of them; I then went round to the cottons, and I observed when I came back again the prisoner's gown in a very awkward manner, as if something were under it; I shewed her several more, but she did not fix on any of them, she liked one pretty well, she said she would determine of it that night, and come the next morning for it; I was taking the prints that I had shewn, to see if there were any which she might like, which she had seen; when I was doing that she turned on her heel and wished me a good night, and went out; I then jumped over the counter, and desired the shopman to run after her, and stop her immediately, which he did, he overtook her about a dozen yards from the door; I followed him likewise myself, and began to feel about for the gown, where I thought the bundle was, then it was gone; the shopman that laid hold of her first, here it lays, I I see him pick it up, I brought her in and had her examined.</p>

               <p>Prisoner. Was there not another man in the shop, looking at goods the same time? - There was, the man was a neighbour.</p>
               <p>Q. What is your man's name? - Atkinson, he is not here, the boy is, I could not possibly bring them both; Atkinson was at the opposite counter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17950916-92-person966">
                  JAMES
                   DAY
               <interp inst="t17950916-92-person966" type="surname" value="DAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-person966" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-person966" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>Q. How old are you? - Seventeen. I am servant to Robert Mac Glew. On Thursday night between eight and nine o'clock the 10th of September last; Mary Moore came into the shop and asked to look at some printed callicoes for a gown; some time after she went out; I see my<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179509160246"></xptr>master shew her a great many goods, and when she went out he told the shopman to stop her, and I immediately went to the door, and we were about a dozen yards from the door, and I see her drop this piece of printed callico, and I see the young man stop her, and he picked it up. There were no other customers in the shop.</p>
               <p>Q. Where was Atkinson? - Behind the opposite counter.</p>
               <p>- SAPWELL sworn.</p>


               <p>I produce the cotton, I received it of the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I am sure it is mine, there are several marks, it has been in the house these six years almost</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I am quite innocent, I have nothing more to say, I hope you will consider that my friends are all in the country, and I have got nobody here to speak for me.</p>
               <p>GUILTY,</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17950916-92-verdict523" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-verdict523" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-92-verdict523" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               Of stealing, but not privately in the shop
            </rs>. (Aged 21.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17950916-92-punish524" type="punishmentDescription">
